  "prompt": "My iPhone screen broke I have iCloud, would notifications I received transfer over to a replacement or would contacts transfer and notifications gone?",
  "response": "When you replace your iPhone and restore it from an iCloud backup, certain types of data are restored, but not all. Here's what you can typically expect:\n\n1. **Contacts**: These will be restored to your new device if they are synced with iCloud. Make sure that your contacts are backed up through iCloud by checking your settings in the iCloud section under your Apple ID.\n\n2. **Notifications**: Notifications are generally not stored in iCloud backups and will not transfer over to your new device. Once a notification is dismissed or the device is backed up, it isn't stored in a way that allows it to be restored to another device. However, you will start receiving all future notifications on your new device once apps are reinstalled and active.\n\nTo ensure a smooth transition, make sure all the relevant apps and data are backed up to iCloud before setting up your replacement iPhone. You can also manually check what data is being synced with iCloud by visiting Settings > [Your Name] > iCloud on your old device if it's still functional to some extent.",
